<Fragment slot="intro">
<p>We repair LG dryers across Irvine — same-day in most cases, typically a 1–2 hour response, and $280–380 for the common fixes. As newer planned-community housing, the call we get most isn't decades of lint — it's a d80 on a near-new machine from a builder vent that's out of LG spec, plus hard-water element wear. Our LG Dryer Repair techs verify and confirm the fault before they quote — call (323) 990-7550.</p>
<p>Irvine is our Orange County home base — we're here every day, know every planned community by name, and understand exactly how the Irvine Company's standardised construction creates service patterns that repeat across the city. The housing stock here is predominantly 2000s through 2020s construction — newer than almost anything we service in LA County. That means different problems. Less about decades of accumulated lint in original vent runs, more about installation issues in new construction, ThinQ smart dryer diagnostics, hard water mineral buildup accelerating heating element wear, and the first wave of 2005–2010 Irvine homes now hitting the 15-year mechanical service window. We have parts for every LG model common in Irvine on the truck. Response time is 1–2 hours.</p>
