<h3>My new LG dryer in my Irvine home shows d80 — is the machine defective?</h3>
<p>Almost certainly not — almost certainly a builder-installed vent out of LG specifications. New construction in Irvine frequently has vent runs with too many bends or total lengths exceeding LG's limits for the specific model. The machine is fine. We verify and correct for $65, waived when we fix the issue. Written vent measurements provided every time.</p>

<h3>Why does my LG dryer keep blowing the thermal fuse in my Irvine home?</h3>
<p>Two most likely causes in Irvine specifically. First: vent restriction from a never-cleaned duct run — fix the vent before replacing the fuse. Second: hard water mineral buildup on the heating element creating hot spots that trip the fuse repeatedly. We check both on every repeated-fuse-failure call in Irvine. Replacing only the fuse without addressing the element means the same call in six months.</p>

<h3>Do you service LG ThinQ smart dryers in Irvine?</h3>
<p>Yes — ThinQ-enabled DLEX and DLGX models are the most common machines in new Irvine construction. Share the ThinQ app error code when you call — we identify the likely cause before we arrive and sometimes arrive with the specific part already on the truck.</p>

<h3>What warranty do you provide on LG dryer repairs in Irvine?</h3>
<p>1-year warranty on both parts and labor on every repair. All parts are OEM LG components. If the same component fails within the warranty period, we return at no charge throughout Irvine and all of Orange County.</p>

<h3>Do you offer same-day LG dryer repair in Irvine?</h3>
<p>Yes — Irvine is our Orange County home base. Typically 1–2 hours from your call. Call (323) 990-7550, Monday through Saturday 8am–7pm, Sunday 9am–5pm.</p>

<h3>Is it worth repairing a premium LG Signature dryer in Irvine, or replacing it?</h3>
<p>Almost always yes — and we see plenty in Shady Canyon and Turtle Rock. An LG Signature DLEX9500V cost $1,500+ new, so a $320–400 drum-bearing or steam-component repair is a small fraction of replacement and buys another decade. Our LG Dryer Repair techs carry premium-model parts, and the $65 diagnostic is waived when you approve the repair. We're licensed with the Bureau of Household Goods and Services (#49573).</p>

<h3>Do you repair stacked LG dryers in Irvine condos?</h3>
<p>Yes — stacked DLGX/DLEX units are common in Oak Creek, Columbus Grove, and Stonegate. We separate the stack, complete the repair, and restack — about 30–45 extra minutes, same pricing, no surcharge — and we swap the kinked foil transition duct for semi-rigid metal, which fixes the persistent d80 these tight closets cause. The $65 diagnostic is waived when you approve the repair.</p>

